83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
Senate Bill 1509
Printed pursuant to Senate Interim Rule 213.28 by order of the President of the Senate in conformance with pre-
session filing rules, indicating neither advocacy nor opposition on the part of the President (at the request
of Senate Interim Committee on Rules and Executive Appointments for Senators Kayse Jama, Bruce Starr)
SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure as introduced. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability
standards.
Digest: The Act allows for the switch of electors of President and Vice President if they do not
vote like they pledged. (Flesch Readability Score: 72.7).
Establishes the qualifications of an elector of President and Vice President of the United States.
Provides the contents of a certificate of ascertainment of electors. Provides that an elector who does
not vote in accordance with the signed pledge of electors vacates the office of elector. Provides for
the filling of the vacancy. Provides for mileage expenses to be given to electors who attend the
meeting of electors and whose ballot is not invalid.
Takes effect on July 1, 2026.
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT
2 Relating to electors of President and Vice President of the United States; amending ORS 248.355,
3 248.370 and 248.380; and prescribing an effective date.
4 Be It Enacted by the People of the State of Oregon:
5 SECTION 1. ORS 248.355 is amended to read:
6 248.355. (1) In a year when a President and Vice President of the United States are to be nom-
7 inated and elected, each political party nominating candidates for those offices shall select a number
8 of candidates for elector of President and Vice President equal to the total number of Senators and
9 Representatives to which this state is entitled in Congress.
10 (2) An individual may be selected as a candidate for elector of President and Vice Presi-
11 dent only if, at the time of the individual’s selection, that individual is:
12 (a) Registered as an elector in this state;
13 (b) If selected under subsection (1) of this section, registered as being affiliated with the
14 party selecting that individual; or
15 (c) If selected to fill a vacancy under ORS 248.370, registered as not being affiliated with
16 any political party.
17 [(2)] (3) Upon being selected, an individual who is selected as a candidate for elector [when
18 selected] shall sign a pledge stating that, if elected under ORS 248.360, the [candidate] individual
19 will vote in the electoral college for the winning candidates [of the party] for President and Vice
20 President, except as provided under ORS 248.370 (6)(b). The Secretary of State shall prescribe the
21 form of the pledge.
22 (4) The party shall certify the names of the selected candidates for elector to the Secretary of
23 State, and provide to the secretary the pledges signed by the candidates under subsection (3)
24 of this section, not later than the 70th day before the election of electors.
25 SECTION 2. ORS 248.370 is amended to read:
26 248.370. (1) The electors of President and Vice President shall convene at the State Capitol on
