1 the first Tuesday after the second Wednesday in December following their election at a time to be
2 established by the Secretary of State by rule.
3 (2) The Secretary of State shall preside over the convening of electors under this section
4 and shall perform any duty as an administrator on behalf of the electors in accordance with
5 the requirements placed on electors under federal law and the laws of this state.
6 [(2)] (3) Not later than six days prior to the convening of electors under subsection (1) of this
7 section, the Governor and the Secretary of State shall issue a certificate of ascertainment of ap-
8 pointment of electors as required by 3 U.S.C. 5. The certificate of ascertainment shall contain:
9 (a) A statement that:
10 (A) The electors listed on the certificate shall serve as electors unless a vacancy occurs
11 in the office of elector prior to the end of the meeting convened under this section;
12 (B) For any vacancy that may occur prior to the end of the meeting convened under this
13 section, the vacancy will be filled at the meeting; and
14 (C) If a vacancy is filled on the day of the meeting of electors, the Governor shall submit
15 an amended certificate of ascertainment certifying the names of the final list of electors who
16 presented valid ballots to the Secretary of State at the meeting; and
17 (b) A security feature or features for the purpose of verifying the authenticity of the certificate.
18 The Secretary of State shall determine by rule the form of the security feature or features under this
19 subsection.
20 [(3)] (4)(a) If there is any vacancy in the office of an elector caused by death, refusal to act,
21 [neglect] failure to attend the meeting of electors or otherwise, the Secretary of State shall
22 declare the vacancy, and the remaining electors present shall fill the vacancy by plurality of
23 voice votes at the time and place of the convening of electors under subsection (1) of this section.
24 The Governor and the Secretary of State shall issue an amended certificate of ascertainment in
25 accordance with the requirements of subsection (3) of this section containing the name of any
26 elector who fills a vacancy under this subsection and indicating that the amended certificate is
27 to be substituted for the certificate that was previously issued under subsection (3) of this
28 section.
29 [(4)] (b) Prior to the voice vote to fill a vacancy under paragraph (a) of this subsection [(3)
30 of this section], a candidate for filling the vacancy shall sign the pledge required under ORS 248.355.
31 (5) When all the electors have appeared and any vacancies have been filled under subsection
32 (4) of this section, the electors shall take and subscribe to an oath of office administered by the
33 Secretary of State. Following the taking of the oath of office under this subsection, the electors shall
34 perform the duties required of them by the Constitution and laws of the United States.
35 (6)(a) Each elector shall complete two ballots, one for President and one for Vice Presi-
36 dent. The elector shall cast a vote for the winning candidate for each office, except as pro-
37 vided under paragraph (b) of this subsection.
38 (b) If the winning candidate for President or Vice President dies or withdraws after the
39 date of the election but before the meeting of electors, the electors shall vote for the re-
40 placement to the winning candidate who is selected in accordance with the rules and bylaws
41 of the political party that nominated the winning candidate.
42 (7) Each elector shall present that elector’s completed ballots for President and Vice
43 President under subsection (6) of this section to the Secretary of State.
44 (8)(a) The Secretary of State shall examine each ballot presented under subsection (7) of
45 this section to determine whether the ballot is completed in accordance with the pledge
